09:28.412 --> 09:32.851
Ho... here we go. He's off.
Put your foot down there, Con.

09:33.115 --> 09:34.228
Something happening, Control.

09:34.331 --> 09:37.146
You're telling me. There's a report
of a robbery at the dole office.

09:37.211 --> 09:40.025
Oh, for fuck's sake, we're just
at the fucking dole office.

09:40.090 --> 09:40.592
What?

09:40.858 --> 09:42.713
Fuck it! What do we do now?

09:48.569 --> 09:49.878
I never promised you a story.

09:49.977 --> 09:50.642
You did!

09:50.746 --> 09:51.477
I did not.

09:51.577 --> 09:52.560
You did so, da!

09:52.634 --> 09:53.779
What did I tell you about lying?

09:53.882 --> 09:56.248
To lie to everyone
except you and ma.

09:56.313 --> 09:58.223
And us.

09:58.745 --> 10:00.371
Oh, yeah, and Auntie Lisa.

10:00.473 --> 10:03.406
And the whole family. You never
lie to anyone in the family.

10:05.240 --> 10:07.858
Tell us the story
about The Mansions, da.

10:07.960 --> 10:11.123
Yeah, da,
tell us about The Mansions.

10:12.951 --> 10:13.933
Fair enough.

10:14.039 --> 10:14.868
Do you want to hear
the whole thing?

10:14.967 --> 10:15.796
From the start.

10:15.895 --> 10:17.356
Okay.

10:18.007 --> 10:20.624
Long, long ago,
years ago before you were born

10:20.726 --> 10:23.214
and your ma and me and Auntie Lisa
were very young

10:23.318 --> 10:25.554
we all lived in a place
called The Mansions.

10:25.622 --> 10:28.076
All our grannies and grand-dads
and brothers

10:28.181 --> 10:31.214
and sisters and all our pals.
It was brilliant.

10:31.317 --> 10:33.935
It was like a big hotel...

10:34.037 --> 10:36.621
built specially for us
and all our mates.

10:37.172 --> 10:38.666
And when I was young,

10:38.772 --> 10:41.707
I used to think
God was smiling down on us.

10:41.813 --> 10:45.073
Putting a special glow around us
so we could do as we pleased.

10:45.140 --> 10:48.587
Go about our business with
no-one getting in our way.

10:48.660 --> 10:50.961
And that it would never change.

10:51.059 --> 10:52.881
Tell us about the bailiffs, da.

10:54.771 --> 10:56.080
All right, so.

10:57.203 --> 10:58.577
Do you know what bailiffs are?

10:58.642 --> 11:00.878
They're just like gods
but they're worse.

11:00.978 --> 11:02.538
Much worse.

11:04.594 --> 11:08.204
So... one day...
this was before you were born.

11:08.273 --> 11:11.339
I was coming home
after working hard all day.

11:11.921 --> 11:15.881
And I saw them -- the bailiffs
attacking our homes.

11:15.984 --> 11:19.083
Big bastards with hammers and
knives and all sorts of things.

11:19.183 --> 11:21.071
But that didn't stop me
when I saw what they were at.

11:21.168 --> 11:22.574
I went for them.

11:22.670 --> 11:23.947
We fought for hours.

11:24.431 --> 11:25.992
But there was too many altogether.

11:26.095 --> 11:27.950
So, your ma and me and Lisa

11:28.047 --> 11:30.729
we barricaded ourselves in
and we wouldn't come out.

11:30.798 --> 11:33.067
You're need gonna take our homes
away from us.

11:33.134 --> 11:34.660
And they couldn't get in,
no matter how hard they tried.

11:34.893 --> 11:37.991
They huffed and they puffed,
but it was no use.

11:39.117 --> 11:40.939
And all around us...

11:41.004 --> 11:42.892
we could hear
the screaming and wailing

11:42.957 --> 11:44.648
of our friends and neighbors

11:44.717 --> 11:47.585
as they tore their houses
to little pieces.

11:47.660 --> 11:49.733
Like savages they were.

11:50.380 --> 11:51.907
They tried everything

11:52.171 --> 11:53.731
but they didn't know me.

11:53.835 --> 11:55.461
I wouldn't budge.

11:55.563 --> 11:57.702
No matter if they brought the
whole place down around our ears.

11:57.931 --> 11:59.208
And then the Mayor came!

11:59.308 --> 12:01.063
That's right.

12:01.131 --> 12:03.749
They were so pissed off
they couldn't get the better of me

12:03.851 --> 12:07.647
the Lord Mayor of Dublin himself
come out to see your da.

12:08.011 --> 12:09.188
Mr. Lynch.

12:11.178 --> 12:12.126
Michael!

12:12.842 --> 12:17.477
Michael! Michael, please,
if you'll just hear me.

12:17.545 --> 12:19.105
Michael...

12:21.224 --> 12:23.080
Get on your knees!

12:23.145 --> 12:24.225
I'm pleading with you!

12:24.330 --> 12:25.987
I personally have been authorized

12:26.089 --> 12:29.766
to offer you these keys
to two houses.

12:29.833 --> 12:31.655
One for us and one for Auntie Lisa.

12:31.753 --> 12:33.475
And I made him promise...

12:33.576 --> 12:36.805
that no-one could ever take
our homes away from us again.

12:37.480 --> 12:39.171
And the Mayor said...

12:39.272 --> 12:43.646
Yes, I promise!

12:43.751 --> 12:46.817
So, I graciously
accepted their offer.

12:47.303 --> 12:50.171
I won. I beat them all.

12:50.246 --> 12:53.093
The bailiff and the Mayor
and the law.

12:53.157 --> 12:56.833
I was loyal.
And that's why I won.

12:57.477 --> 12:59.517
You see, the thing is...

12:59.589 --> 13:01.247
they'll never beat you...

13:01.349 --> 13:05.057
if you stick together
and stay loyal.

13:17.988 --> 13:19.929
Are they asleep?

13:22.147 --> 13:25.278
It's time
for the tickle man.

13:30.433 --> 13:31.382
See you tomorrow.

13:32.290 --> 13:33.238
'Night.

13:52.318 --> 13:53.180
Hiya, Michael.

13:53.278 --> 13:54.588
Hey, Shaun.

14:04.127 --> 14:05.076
