I'm gonna tell you about.

18:54.366 --> 18:56.122
Look, I understand.

18:56.222 --> 18:58.360
While I'm talking I'll make
some crack about the Provos,

18:58.462 --> 18:59.508
you watch how he reacts.

18:59.613 --> 19:01.303
Tommy, come on, we're going.

19:01.404 --> 19:02.298
Say goodbye to daddy.

19:02.397 --> 19:03.160
Bue-bye, da.

19:03.261 --> 19:04.155
By, chicken.

19:04.221 --> 19:05.235
Bye lads.

19:05.340 --> 19:06.748
Bye.

19:06.846 --> 19:08.055
Bye, da.

19:09.244 --> 19:10.870
All right, sitting down, lads.

19:11.580 --> 19:12.474
One more round, Michael?

19:12.540 --> 19:13.850
Little fella, sit down.

19:13.948 --> 19:15.289
All right...

19:16.540 --> 19:19.027
First, you've all met Shay Kirby.

19:19.131 --> 19:20.243
How's it going?

19:21.531 --> 19:22.959
Now, as you know...

19:23.067 --> 19:26.995
I may be a bit occupied in the
Four Courts come Monday week.

19:27.099 --> 19:29.073
Now, should go okay,
but you never know.

19:29.179 --> 19:30.901
So I thought maybe now is the time

19:31.001 --> 19:32.179
for a job I've been thinking about
the last few months.

19:32.281 --> 19:34.616
One of those impossible ones.

19:34.713 --> 19:37.364
Now, this is one the IRA
had their piggy little eyes on

19:37.433 --> 19:39.505
but even they thought
it couldn't be done.

19:39.577 --> 19:42.326
Well, lads, when I heard that
I thought to myself,

19:42.424 --> 19:44.661
we're gonna have to show
those dozy fuckers a thing or two

19:44.729 --> 19:48.306
about robbing
O'Donnell's jewellery factory.

19:48.376 --> 19:49.303
Jesus Christ, Michael.

19:49.367 --> 19:50.960
Bollocks, man!

19:51.063 --> 19:52.852
What I was thinking was...

19:52.951 --> 19:56.945
we wouldn't actually try to
break into the factory itself

19:57.047 --> 20:01.423
but we'd sort of drop in.

20:09.973 --> 20:12.078
Fuck. Jesus Christ!

20:22.101 --> 20:25.582
And then sort of camp
out in the yard

20:25.685 --> 20:29.645
until someone arrives to let us
in the next morning.

20:29.749 --> 20:30.993
And that someone...

20:31.092 --> 20:33.067
is Mr. Fintan Doorley
the General Manager.

20:33.172 --> 20:36.237
Like myself, very precise man.

20:36.339 --> 20:39.754
Fintan arrives
at five-to-eight every morning.

20:39.860 --> 20:42.761
Now, as a man
who likes and needs routine

20:42.835 --> 20:45.835
he will probably be
a bit surprised at what he sees.

20:53.682 --> 20:56.333
Good morning, Mr. Doorley.
We're here to steal your gold.

20:56.434 --> 20:57.840
Meet our esteemed leader.

20:57.938 --> 20:59.083
Good morning, staff.

20:59.185 --> 21:01.290
Identify yourselves.

21:05.232 --> 21:07.534
Once inside
they'll meet Tony, Tom and Billy

21:07.632 --> 21:09.836
who'll invite them
to step into the marquee.

21:09.936 --> 21:12.325
And lads... Politely, okay?

21:12.400 --> 21:13.741
As long as
they're doing us no harm,

21:13.808 --> 21:15.334
we won't do them any harm.

21:15.407 --> 21:17.382
Stop mucking around.
Do as you're told!

21:17.488 --> 21:19.048
You got that, Billy?

21:19.119 --> 21:19.947
What?

21:20.047 --> 21:21.061
Just get the people inside.

21:21.166 --> 21:23.076
Blow up the air bed, love,
I'l be in in a minute.

21:23.182 --> 21:24.110
That's enough out of you, Billy.

21:24.207 --> 21:25.613
Give us a kiss,
you big ride, you.

21:26.254 --> 21:27.912
Yeah, yeah. Okay, Michael.

21:38.668 --> 21:41.734
So that at quarter-to-nine,
we all drive back out again.

21:41.964 --> 21:43.371
And we can all relax

21:43.468 --> 21:46.728
because it will be some time before
anyone gets to call the Gardai.

21:49.291 --> 21:52.138
Now does everyone have a picture
of that in their minds?

21:53.098 --> 21:56.808
Because, lads, I promise...

21:56.874 --> 22:01.477
that's just the way
it's gonne be easy as pie.

22:04.489 --> 22:06.212
What age are you, Alec?

22:06.313 --> 22:08.417
What, ten years younger than me?

22:08.521 --> 22:09.765
Big difference.

22:10.152 --> 22:12.672
Then Tony and Michael,
add another ten years on to that.

22:13.065 --> 22:14.974
Now, when they were kids
they had fuck all.

22:15.080 --> 22:16.486
Ain't that right, Michael?

22:16.583 --> 22:17.183
We had each other.

22:17.415 --> 22:18.659
True.

22:19.847 --> 22:22.236
Now, I'm that much younger
so I got some stuff,

22:22.343 --> 22:24.131
but it was never the right stuff.

22:24.231 --> 22:25.376
What are you
shitting on about, man?

22:25.447 --> 22:27.235
Billy, Billy knows
what I'm talking about, don't you?

22:27.334 --> 22:28.678
No.

22:28.936 --> 22:30.277
For fuck's sake.

22:30.376 --> 22:32.797
What was the big thing
when you were eight, say?

22:32.872 --> 22:34.814
''Star Wars'', I suppose.
Is that what you mean?

22:34.919 --> 22:35.901
''Star Wars''.

22:36.008 --> 22:38.113
Now, I bet you got the proper
''Star Wars'' stuff.

22:38.215 --> 22:40.669
You know, the real toys.
What were they called?

22:40.774 --> 22:42.749
Luke Skywalker, Darth Vader,
I had all that shite, man.

22:42.854 --> 22:44.709
And it was the proper thing, yeah?
The official stuff?

22:44.774 --> 22:46.301
Yeah, so what?

22:46.406 --> 22:47.650
So, I never got that.

22:48.517 --> 22:50.241
But, sure, me da probably robbed
the fucking things anyway.

22:50.341 --> 22:51.454
It doesn't matter!

22:52.005 --> 22:54.307
My ma and da couldn't even rob
the proper thing.

22:55.780 --> 22:57.689
That's a fucking tragedy, Stevie.

22:58.756 --> 23:00.283
It is a fucking tragedy.

23:00.388 --> 23:03.868
Fellas your age,
you got the proper thing.

23:03.971 --> 23:06.841
And now my kids want
every fucking thing that's going.

23:06.947 --> 23:08.289
And you're gonna use
all your money

23:08.388 --> 23:09.697
to make sure they get it.
Fair play to you.

23:09.763 --> 23:11.137
In me hole.

23:13.122 --> 23:15.227
I'm gonna make up for all the stuff
I missed out on.

23:15.330 --> 23:18.364
I'm gonna enjoy myself.

23:26.434 --> 23:27.862
Go ahead Tom.

23:29.313 --> 23:30.261
Right, Michael.

23:31.457 --> 23:33.846
Now, the depth of this door
is just right.

23:35.136 --> 23:38.365
Now, once that panel is removed
the bars sit in there,

23:38.432 --> 23:40.407
nice and snug.

23:40.512 --> 23:42.781
Now, if you have enough of them,
they don't rattle around.

23:45.311 --> 23:47.199
And you don't even notice
the extra weight

23:47.295 --> 23:49.531
when you're opening
and closing the door.

23:51.454 --> 23:54.487
Now this couple I've lined up
they're complete innocents

23:54.590 --> 23:55.800
that's the beauty of it

23:55.902 --> 23:57.625
no extra splits.

23:57.726 --> 23:59.580
They're just
old friends of me da's.

23:59.677 --> 24:02.841
Couple in their fifties
Mr. and Mrs. Harmless.

24:02.909 --> 24:04.185
And you know Customs...

24:04.253 --> 24:08.278
while they're busy searching
bearded ex-hippies in their 2CVs

24:08.380 --> 24:11.131
they'll be tipping
their hats at our pair

24:11.229 --> 24:12.658
as they chugger, chugger through

24:12.733 --> 24:14.391
at their usual
twenty-five miles an hour.

24:14.492 --> 24:16.859
Then they drive all the way over
to the Cotswolds.

24:16.956 --> 24:19.290
They've told me all about
this lovely hotel

24:19.356 --> 24:22.226
it's so quiet and peaceful that
they always go back every year.

24:24.603 --> 24:26.545
This is how I see it all happening,
Michael.

24:26.971 --> 24:30.004
It's not too far from Birmingham,
right,

24:30.075 --> 24:31.700
so I can fly in be at their hotel
inwhat, half an hour.

24:31.802 --> 24:35.152
They'll be there taking afternoon tea
completely unaware

24:35.227 --> 24:36.853
that they've a couple of
hundred thousand quids'

24:36.956 --> 24:39.027
worth of gold
sitting outside in the car.

24:44.666 --> 24:47.513
There'll be no more than,
what a dozen cars parked there

24:47.609 --> 24:50.097
no security, so getting
at the car'll be no problem.

24:50.169 --> 24:52.144
Bing, bang, boom. Get the gold

24:52.249 --> 24:53.143
bring it to the fence.

24:53.241 --> 24:55.379
Tom, it all sounds fine.

24:55.640 --> 24:57.582
I'll see you when you get back, so.

24:58.584 --> 25:02.412
Don't worry about it, Michael.
You can trust me.

25:06.519 --> 25:08.112
Hi, Uncle Billy.

25:09.559 --> 25:12.405
Come here to me, chicken.
Come here to me.

25:14.806 --> 25:15.788
Oh, look at you.

25:15.862 --> 25:17.966
My God,
are you an angel or a princess?

25:18.069 --> 25:18.931
Isn't she gorgeous?

25:19.029 --> 25:21.931
Come here to me. Tell me this would
that buy a few rosary beads eh?

25:23.573 --> 25:25.362
Come here.
What do you say to Mr. Higgins?

25:25.461 --> 25:25.929
Thank you.

25:26.036 --> 25:27.018
No problem, love.

25:27.252 --> 25:28.299
Good girl, good girl.
Now, come here to me, listen.

25:28.372 --> 25:29.201
Go on uupstairs, right,

25:29.300 --> 25:30.248
and I'll be with you
in a few minutes.

25:30.356 --> 25:31.152
All right, chicken, go on.

25:31.252 --> 25:33.227
Save us a dance, love,
will you?

25:36.019 --> 25:37.513
Who's your man there
with Billy?

25:37.619 --> 25:38.961
Higgins is his name.

25:39.411 --> 25:42.639
Grew up around here all right.
Went to college, you know.

25:42.706 --> 25:44.615
IRA I heard.

25:44.690 --> 25:48.105
Funny thing, he looks more like you
than your brother does.

25:48.178 --> 25:49.519
Same haircut anyway.

25:49.617 --> 25:50.828
Yeah, yeah.

25:53.330 --> 25:54.279
I'm telling you.

25:54.354 --> 25:56.110
Yeah, I know, I'm not gonna
fuck it up all right?

25:58.193 --> 25:59.272
Thanks for the lift.

25:59.345 --> 26:01.866
Da, da, look what granny gave me.

26:01.937 --> 26:03.082
What is it, chicken?

26:03.185 --> 26:06.567
It's a holy book
with lots of pictures.

26:06.672 --> 26:08.233
Oh, isn't that brilliant?

26:08.496 --> 26:10.187
What I'd give to
have a present like that.

26:12.112 --> 26:13.769
That's what I'd like to know
where did you come from?

26:13.871 --> 26:14.951
Guess.

26:15.215 --> 26:19.755
Mickey, you know that job that
Tom was doing for you in England?

26:20.015 --> 26:21.509
Yeah.

26:21.582 --> 26:24.038
What I mean, Mike,
even though I always knew that

26:24.109 --> 26:26.892
Tom was a bit of a fucking eject
you know, he was sound.

26:26.989 --> 26:29.803
I mean, if you'd asked me
that's what I'd have told you.

26:32.109 --> 26:35.338
Looks like
he's done a runner and...

26:35.405 --> 26:37.477
there's no car and there's no gold.

26:37.580 --> 26:39.271
Yeah.

26:40.365 --> 26:41.609
So what do you wanna do?

26:42.221 --> 26:44.609
Why the fuck did he think
he could get away with it?

26:44.684 --> 26:46.178
It's not like him,
I'll say that for him.

26:46.636 --> 26:49.157
And mind you, can you ever
trust anyone these days?

26:49.260 --> 26:51.649
Yeah, you can.
That's what it's all about.

26:51.724 --> 26:54.090
Wouldn't have asked him to
do the job if I didn't trust him.

26:56.683 --> 26:57.632
What now?

26:57.739 --> 26:59.495
You go find him. Bring him back.

26:59.595 --> 27:01.187
Okay.

27:01.290 --> 27:01.857
Tony...

27:01.962 --> 27:02.725
Yeah?

27:02.794 --> 27:04.801
You can finish your dinner first.

27:15.337 --> 27:17.508
Jesus, are you gonna queue up?

27:17.576 --> 27:20.609
I'll have to, won't I
unless you've any better ideas?

27:20.712 --> 27:23.046
Well, I can get you in there
no bother. Private tour.

27:23.304 --> 27:25.758
No, thanks,
I'll try the front door.

27:25.863 --> 27:27.423
Fair enough.
Listen, I've gotta go.

27:27.527 --> 27:29.731
Got this stupid fucking court thing
in half-an-hour.

27:29.799 --> 27:30.748
Enjoy yourself.

27:31.016 --> 27:32.869
I will.
You'll be all right, will you?

27:32.967 --> 27:34.211
Course.

27:40.710 --> 27:43.579
My Lord, may I request
an adjournment of proceedings

27:43.686 --> 27:44.579
until Wednesday?

27:44.678 --> 27:46.434
Application refused.

27:46.534 --> 27:47.809
but, my Lord, Mr. Harrison...

27:47.909 --> 27:53.092
the prosecution is ready,
the jury is ready, I am ready.

27:53.189 --> 27:57.498
Your client cannot avoid
the process of law indefinitely.

27:57.572 --> 28:00.801
Mr. McHale, are you ready to begin?

28:00.900 --> 28:02.209
Certainly, my Lord.

28:05.091 --> 28:08.058
Almost two years ago
on the nineteenth of February

28:08.323 --> 28:11.007
the defendant, Michael Lynch
and an unknown associate

28:11.234 --> 28:14.234
entered the premises of Superex
a video game company.

28:14.338 --> 28:16.313
They were armed and dangerous.

28:16.386 --> 28:18.590
They threatened the life
of a member of staff

28:18.690 --> 28:21.559
and stole over
thirty-two thousand pounds in cash.

28:23.905 --> 28:24.798
Listen, Michael...

28:26.689 --> 28:28.095
See this?

28:29.568 --> 28:30.461
Yeah?

28:31.008 --> 28:32.502
Can I hang it up in our room?

28:32.608 --> 28:34.364
What do you want
a holy picture for?

28:34.720 --> 28:36.922
It's not a holy picture,
it's a Caravaggio.

28:37.182 --> 28:38.426
He's about as holy as you are.

28:38.527 --> 28:39.989
Well, it looks like
a holy picture to me.

28:40.095 --> 28:41.557
Can I hang it up, or can't I?

28:42.175 --> 28:42.644
Of course.

28:42.910 --> 28:44.284
And you wont' be
slagging me about it?

28:44.350 --> 28:45.757
I promise.

28:46.527 --> 28:47.672
Grand.

28:51.038 --> 28:52.696
Can I go to the toilet, da?

28:52.797 --> 28:53.910
Of course.

28:55.390 --> 28:57.757
Do you get the feeling
I don't believe you, Tom?

28:58.556 --> 29:02.713
Please, Michael... please!
I swear...

29:02.813 --> 29:04.406
I mean, even if it is true,
these old ones

29:04.509 --> 29:06.483
got their car door
ripped off by a passing Land Rover

29:06.556 --> 29:08.596
and then left it abandoned
on the side of the road.

29:08.859 --> 29:11.314
I searched, Michael.
I drove up and down.

29:11.387 --> 29:14.551
I found the car and I even
put a new door on it an' all.

29:14.652 --> 29:19.027
I fucked up, you know,
and I was, I was afraid.

29:19.100 --> 29:21.783
So you don't think
I'm a fair man then, Tom?

29:22.523 --> 29:23.450
No.

29:23.866 --> 29:26.649
No, it's not, it's not that,
Michael, it's...

29:28.379 --> 29:33.047
Please, Michael...
I'm sorry, please.

29:34.202 --> 29:35.958
What did you do with the gold?

29:36.058 --> 29:37.781
Oh, God...

29:39.033 --> 29:41.007
I did nothing!

29:41.113 --> 29:43.862
I never got it, I never!

29:44.409 --> 29:47.223
It's gone. You have to believe me.

29:47.767 --> 29:49.077
But you ran away, Tom.

29:49.560 --> 29:51.981
Only scumbags run away.

29:52.088 --> 29:53.996
You can't trust someone
who does that, can you?

29:54.103 --> 29:55.564
I mean, would you trust them, Tom?
Would you?

29:55.831 --> 29:57.936
No, no, I wouldn't.

30:08.374 --> 30:11.221
So you see why this is a problem
I have to deal with, don't you?

30:11.286 --> 30:13.555
I mean, I can't leave it
hanging around, can I?

30:13.654 --> 30:14.636
Yeah, I know...

30:14.741 --> 30:16.083
Where's the gold?

30:16.182 --> 30:17.555
I don't know.

30:22.037 --> 30:23.411
What do you think?

30:23.636 --> 30:26.057
I don't know, Michael, I...

30:27.827 --> 30:31.472
I'm not certain...
or anything like...

30:31.540 --> 30:32.849
I'd nearly believe him, Michael.

30:32.948 --> 30:33.895
Yeah, I think you're right.

30:34.163 --> 30:37.163
His story is so stupid
it's probably true.

30:37.651 --> 30:39.178
All rigth, let him down.

30:42.770 --> 30:45.356
I'm sorry, Tom.
I believe your story now.

30:45.617 --> 30:47.919
Tony'll take you to the hospital.

30:48.626 --> 30:49.737
Oh, you're on the medical card,
aren't you?

30:49.808 --> 30:51.816
I mean this won't
cost you anything, will it?

30:51.889 --> 30:52.620
No.

30:52.689 --> 30:54.991
Grand, night. Lads.

30:58.737 --> 31:00.231
And will the accused sit up

31:00.305 --> 31:03.621
and let us see his face, please!

31:05.328 --> 31:08.110
The accused is a very clever man.

31:08.176 --> 31:10.893
But the extraordinary thing
about him

31:10.992 --> 31:13.096
is that he seems unable to resist

31:13.198 --> 31:16.581
letting the rest of the world
know how clever he is.

31:16.686 --> 31:18.574
sometimes I think
he's not a real criminal at all,

31:18.671 --> 31:21.125
he's just a big show-off.

31:33.196 --> 31:34.211
How are things, Michael?

31:34.316 --> 31:35.527
Fair, Shay.
What'll you have?

31:35.628 --> 31:36.838
No, I'm grand.

31:39.436 --> 31:40.897
Is everything all right,
Michael?

31:42.316 --> 31:43.876
Yeah, fine.

31:44.683 --> 31:49.669
Oh, it's just this...
there's this judge...

31:49.930 --> 31:51.785
he's getting on my nerves.

31:51.883 --> 31:55.265
He's prejudiced, you know.

31:55.337 --> 31:56.101
Is that right?

31:59.146 --> 32:02.822
That's his daughter's car.
Do you think you could find it?

32:03.849 --> 32:05.409
Consider it done.

32:08.200 --> 32:10.720
Trial's supposed to end
on Thursday

32:10.984 --> 32:13.886
will that give you enough time
to send them a bit of a message?

32:14.312 --> 32:15.327
A ''frightener''?

32:15.431 --> 32:19.074
It has to be timed just right.

32:19.878 --> 32:21.252
Give me the keys, love.

32:21.927 --> 32:23.007
Thanks for the lunch, sir...

32:23.110 --> 32:24.833
and a very stimulating
conversation.

32:28.262 --> 32:30.880
Bye, dad. Hope we didn't
outstay our welcome.

32:31.142 --> 32:32.385
Not at all, Moira.

32:32.485 --> 32:34.373
Mind you, he does like the osund of
his own voice, doesn't he?

32:34.437 --> 32:39.194
You're one to talk.

32:42.757 --> 32:44.546
In conclusion...

32:44.613 --> 32:46.849
whatever the jury's feelings
may be...

32:46.949 --> 32:51.999
as to what seems
the just conclusion to draw...

32:52.260 --> 32:54.333
I must remind you that...

32:54.435 --> 32:59.421
if the available evidence is not
sufficient for a conviction

32:59.524 --> 33:01.793
then...

33:02.787 --> 33:05.634
you must not convict.

33:08.898 --> 33:11.450
This is another disaster
for the Gardai, isn't it?

33:11.554 --> 33:13.081
Mr. Lynch has been found not guilty.

33:13.345 --> 33:15.233
That is not to say that the Gardai

33:15.330 --> 33:19.158
are pursuing anyone else
in connection with this crime.

33:19.265 --> 33:20.410
It's also not to say that

33:20.481 --> 33:22.335
the Gardai will
cease its investigations

33:22.401 --> 33:23.677
in the activities
of Mr. Michael Lynch.

33:24.257 --> 33:26.167
Do you think the justice system is
too soft on criminals, Michael?

33:26.273 --> 33:28.028
Michael, how can you afford such
an expensive legal team, Mr. Lynch?

33:28.129 --> 33:29.339
Are you back on the dole, Michael?

33:29.441 --> 33:31.896
Now that you're innocent,
can you show us your face?

33:31.969 --> 33:32.951
Daddy.

33:33.025 --> 33:34.454
There's daddy
with the black hood on him.

33:34.559 --> 33:35.639
That's right.

33:35.711 --> 33:36.889
Da, why are you wearing
a black hood?

33:36.991 --> 33:38.333
Cos, I don't want them to see me.

33:38.432 --> 33:41.149
...that Mr. Michael Lynch
is not a funny man.

33:41.216 --> 33:42.709
All right, now, kids, who is he?

33:42.782 --> 33:44.059
A Garda.

33:44.158 --> 33:45.086
Is he a pig, da?

33:45.183 --> 33:46.328
You're both right,
but you never call him a pig.

33:46.430 --> 33:47.324
Pay attention to him,
call him a Garda

33:47.423 --> 33:49.245
and never trust him
or anyone like him.

33:49.343 --> 33:51.447
Come on, play it, Michael.
Are me and Lisa in it?

33:51.710 --> 33:53.051
It's just a little bit
